1. Get a platform
2. Get a device/devices
3. Create a context
4. Create a command queue/s for different devices
5. Create a .cl file
6. Build the program
7. Compile the program
8. Setup the kernel

/* For Mandelbrot */

9. Set up xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax (HARDCODE IF NEEDED)
10. Populate the array malloced for storing the range of the possible values ie. the real values and the imaginary values.
11. Create the buffers corresponding to the arrays created in the previous step.
12. Write the values from the arrays which have the inputs to the corresponding buffers.
13. Perform EnqueueNDRangeKernel
14. Print the output from the output buffer by doing clEnqueueReadBuffer.
15. Clear/Flush/Free all the data structures.



